[09:44] <Voldenet> people writing `my (a, b, c) = (a, b, c)` or `my (a, b, c) = @x` want to "assign first value to first item" and so on, and Z= turns that assignment into boring `my a = @x[0]; my b = @x[1]; my c = @x[2]`

